# Content Creation Guidelines

## When to Use Which Skill

### Evolutionary Project Content

**Use `create_evolution_post`** when:
- Content belongs to a specific project and evolution
- Building upon previous architectural decisions
- Part of a systematic learning journey
- Documenting implementation within an evolution

**Use `scaffold_new_evolution`** when:
- Moving to next phase of existing project
- Introducing new technology stack or architecture
- Ready to start a new evolution

**Use `scaffold_new_project`** when:
- Starting a completely new evolutionary project
- New domain to explore systematically
- Want to track progress through multiple evolutions

### Standalone Content

**Use `create_generic_post`** when:
- One-off tutorial or guide
- General learning insights
- Not part of evolutionary journey
- Quick notes or experiments

## Post Quality Standards (Universal)

### All Posts MUST Include

- **Clear, descriptive title**: Accurately describes the content
- **Proper categorization**: Uses appropriate categories (see `_data/config.yml → content_standards.categories`)
- **Code examples with syntax highlighting**: When showing implementation
- **Key learnings or conclusion section**: What was learned or accomplished

### Evolution Posts MUST Additionally Include

- **Evolution Context section**: Auto-generated by `create_evolution_post` skill from `_data/evolutions.yml`
- **Links to related posts**: In same evolution via `{% include evolution/evolution-posts.html %}`
- **Navigation includes**: `{% include evolution/post-navigation.html %}`
- **Reference to previous/next evolution**: When applicable

